{{notability|Institutions|date=March 2015}} {{Infobox university |name = Institute for Medical Engineering and Science |image = [[File:IMES-logo.jpg|250px]] |established = 2012 |city = [[Cambridge, Massachusetts|Cambridge]] |state = [[Massachusetts]] |country = [[United States]] |affiliations = [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology|MIT]] | website = {{URL|imes.mit.edu}} | coor = {{coord|42.3616667|-71.0866667|format=dms|display=inline,title|type:edu_region:US-MA}} }}
The '''Institute for Medical Engineering and Science''' or '''IMES''' is a research institute at the [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]] that aims to combine engineering, medicine, and science to solve challenges in human health.<ref name=IMESAbout>{{cite web|title=Vision - Institute for Medical Engineering & Science|url=http://imes.mit.edu/about/vision/|publisher=Institute for Medical Engineering and Science at MIT|accessdate=12 July 2018}}</ref> The institute was established in 2012 and is currently directed by [[Elazer Edelman]].<ref name=EdelmanDirector>{{cite web|title=Elazer Edelman named director of Institute for Medical Engineering and Science|url=http://news.mit.edu/2018/elazer-edelman-named-director-mit-institute-medical-engineering-science-imes-0430|publisher=MIT News|accessdate=12 July 2018}}</ref>
At MIT, IMES serves to bring together scientific advances with clinical medicine by serving as the point of intersection with major hospitals and industry partners. IMES also serves as the MIT home for the [[Harvard-MIT Division of Health Sciences and Technology]], an educational program administered jointly through Harvard and MIT.
